body_html:
there seems to be a way to print out all variables: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/9298278/cmake-print-out-all-accessible-variables-in-a-script

And then you can print out cached variables: cmake -LA. You can invert to get uncached variables.

body:
there seems to be a way to print out all variables: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/9298278/cmake-print-out-all-accessible-variables-in-a-script

And then you can print out cached variables: `cmake -LA`. You can invert to get uncached variables.
